  "issue_title": "[BUG] Deprecated asyncio.get_event_loop() still in use in validator init and test helpers",
  "issue_body": "## Description\n\n`asyncio.get_event_loop()` is deprecated since Python 3.10 when no running event loop exists, and scheduled to raise `RuntimeError` in future CPython releases. PR #395 migrated `miner_check` and `miner_post` off this API, but four call sites were left behind:\n\n- `neurons/base/validator.py:73` \u2014 `self.loop = asyncio.get_event_loop()` in `BaseValidatorNeuron.__init__`.\n- `tests/validator/test_pat_handler.py:23` \u2014 inside the `_run(coro)` helper.\n- `tests/validator/test_repo_scan.py:40` \u2014 inside the `_run(coro)` helper.\n- `tests/validator/test_issue_discovery_repo_scan.py:41` \u2014 inline call inside `_run_scan`.\n\nThese emit `DeprecationWarning` on every validator test run today and will break when CPython upgrades the warning to an error.\n\n## Steps to Reproduce\n\n1. `git checkout test && uv sync --extra dev`\n2. `uv run pytest tests/validator/test_pat_handler.py -q`\n3. Observe the deprecation warning in the summary:\n\n   ```\n   tests/validator/test_pat_handler.py:23: DeprecationWarning: There is no current event loop\n     return asyncio.get_event_loop().run_until_complete(coro)\n   ```\n\n4. Run strict mode to confirm it would fail when CPython escalates the warning:\n\n   ```\n   uv run pytest tests/validator/test_pat_handler.py -W error::DeprecationWarning -q\n   ```\n\n5. `grep -rn \"asyncio\\.get_event_loop\" neurons/ gittensor/ tests/` confirms the four remaining sites.\n\n## Expected Behavior\n\nNo deprecation warnings. `pytest -W error::DeprecationWarning` should pass across `tests/validator/` and `tests/utils/`. The validator's cached event loop at `BaseValidatorNeuron.__init__` should be created explicitly rather than implicitly acquired from a deprecated API.\n\n## Actual Behavior\n\n`DeprecationWarning: There is no current event loop` is emitted on every validator test run, and `BaseValidatorNeuron.__init__` relies on a deprecated API to create the long-lived loop that `self.loop.run_until_complete(self.concurrent_forward())` uses every step on the background thread.\n\n## Environment\n\n- OS: Linux (Ubuntu 24.04 LTS kernel 6.8.0)\n- Python version: 3.12.3\n- Commit/Version: `bad35f7` on branch `test` (HEAD as of 2026-04-21)\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-04-21T14:49:54.000Z",
